snippet.title: La Doble Vida De Amber Heard Completamente Revelada
snippet.description:
Amber Heard tiene una impresionante carrera en el cine, pero es probable que también conozcas por su vida personal, que muchas veces fue el centro de atención de los medios. Estas son algunas cosas que tal vez no sabías sobre la vida de Amber Heard.

Heard y su ahora ex-esposo Johnny Depp se conocieron en el 2012 en el set de Diario de un Seductor y se casaron en el 2015. En mayo del 2016, Heard solicitó el divorcio y lo acusó de abuso doméstico. Heard escribió en la declaración,

"Durante toda nuestra relación, Johnny fue verbal y físicamente abusivo conmigo. Soporté un excesivo abuso emocional, verbal y físico de Johnny, que ha incluido ataques furiosos, hostiles, humillantes y amenazantes hacia mí cada vez que yo cuestionaba su autoridad o no estaba de acuerdo con él."

Heard también presentó una foto en donde aparece con la cara lastimada. Afirmó que la herida fue causada por un golpe de Depp con su teléfono. Ella le dijo al tribunal,

"Vivo con el temor de que Johnny vuelva a [nuestra casa] sin avisar para aterrorizarme, física y emocionalmente."

Pero la policía no encontró pruebas de ninguna agresión cuando respondió a una llamada por pelea doméstica en la casa de la pareja en mayo del 2016, y Heard se negó a presentar una denuncia penal. El abogado de Depp le dijo a la corte,

"[Heard] está intentando asegurar una resolución financiera prematura alegando abuso. Johnny no puede protegerse a sí mismo ni a Amber del escrutinio de los medios."

Mientras que Heard acusó a Depp de violencia doméstica, ella fue arrestada por presunta violencia doméstica contra su ex pareja, la fotógrafa Tasya van Ree, en septiembre del 2009. Según TMZ, Heard y van Ree discutieron en un aeropuerto, y Heard presuntamente golpeó a van Ree. Fue arrestada y fichada por un delito menor de violencia doméstica, pero el fiscal se negó a seguir adelante con el caso, porque ambas mujeres vivían en California.

Años después, van Ree dijo públicamente que el incidente fue "sobresensacionalizado," y describió a los oficiales que hicieron el arresto como "homofóbicos" - pero en realidad la oficial es una mujer gay, y escribió en Facebook,

"¡No soy homofóbica en lo absoluto! [...] El arresto se hizo porque hubo una agresión (yo lo presencié) y las partes involucradas estaban en una relación doméstica."

Van Ree también emitió una declaración cuando los informes del arresto resurgieron en el 2016, diciendo,

"Es desgarrador que la integridad y la historia de Amber sean cuestionadas una vez más. Amber es una mujer brillante, honesta y hermosa y tengo el mayor respeto por ella. Compartimos 5 maravillosos años juntas y mantenemos contacto hasta el día de hoy."

#AmberHeard

snippet.title: Johnny Depp SPEAKS OUT On How Amber Heard Has RUINED His Career!
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp has recently broken his silence in an interview about his current state in the defamation lawsuit and his career years after he lost his British libel suit. You might remember that in November of 2020, Johnny Depp lost a libel case against British news publisher The Sun after labelling him something he still denies up to this day. This lost libel case might seem to be just a little stain in his long running career, but it actually dealt a huge blow to Johnny. After he lost this libel case, he was kicked out of his recurring role in the J.K Rowling critically acclaimed Fantastic Beasts trilogy, where he would have played the iconic Grindelwald in the series’ third installment. He was then replaced by Mads Mikkelsen in the role. But this was just the start of a harrowing journey in Johnny’s career. He was also kicked out of one of his most famous film series, Walt Disney’s Pirates of the Caribbean and in any of its succeeding films, series, and spin-offs. This libel case really did damage a lot, even the iconic Jack Sparrow. Now, after all the chaos that has swirled around the actor in the past few years, he is almost at the end of it all as his 50 million dollar suit against his ex wife Amber Heard is advancing on its current state of trial. However, although it may seem that Johnny obviously has a lot of advantages over the Aquaman actress in many ways, it still cannot be denied that the whole whirlwind situation really did take a toll on his career, and as he even termed it, the Hollywood industry itself “boycotted” him during his predicament, especially that after all that he has gone through with his roles, his new film “Minamata” will not be released in the United States after all. But why did the award winning actor feel that way and what did he say about it? What made Johnny Depp speak up just recently, after years of keeping his silence, about Hollywood ruining his career? Let’s find out the answer to that in this video. But before all else, make sure to hit that subscribe button first and smash that notification bell for more updates on the Johnny Depp - Amber Heard case. Now, let’s begin!

You may all vividly remember the event in 2017 that started all this frenzy surrounding the now 58 year old actor Johnny Depp and his ex wife Amber Heard. Well, what we did not know back then was how greatly it would affect the actor’s career in the years to come. Inside those four long years of the Johnny and Amber unending turmoil, here is what happened so far that escalated the fire that has already been burning up since 2017: In 2018, Amber wrote an op ed article in The Washington Post where she spoke up and explained how she was hurt and maltreated, and in which she also spoke about the treatment of many other women in the same types of cases. Despite not involving Johnny’s name on her statement, Johnny’s team knew that it was pertained to him, having recently filed a restraining order for physical complaints against him and, well, technically they just got out of their failed relationship. So, in March of 2019, the then 57 year old actor took action and filed a lawsuit of $50 million dollars against the Aquaman actress, for words said over the said aforementioned article in the Washington Post. 

The evidence include a recorded phone call where Amber admitted to hitting Johnny, the actresses’ alleged affairs with actor James Franco and mega businessman Elon Musk, which may have been proved somehow by itself when the two dated for a whole year right after Johnny and Amber’s divorce, and the missing $7 million dollar settlement money that Amber received from the divorce.

During all this havoc, Johnny’s career has almost turned into shambles. The production company also admitted that the decision was made after Amber’s article. Johnny just lost two film series that he is pulling off while Amber Heard continues to get huge parts in huge films. Because of this, fans continue to be upset, and even though they have once been turned down in their past petition to convince Warner Brothers to fire Amber Heard, they are still willing to do it all over again. On the first day of the second Aquaman movie’s filming, #FireAmberHeard trended.

Throughout all of these, Johnny Depp has kept his silence. 

So, is Johnny Depp’s career really in shambles? 

Johnny might still be in an unknown and disastrous chapter in his life, but once everything has gone back to the way they were, we do hope to see Johnny’s career skyrocket back to where it was before.

That’s all for today, if you enjoyed that video, make sure to like, subscribe, and hit that notification bell for more videos like this. Stay tuned!

snippet.title: "She Deserves Jail Time" Johnny Depp Speaks On Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp Reveals What He Think Should Happen To Amber Heard For What She Did.

✅ Subscribe & HIT that notification bell for more Celebrity Content!

Are we finally witnessing the curtains being lowered on Johnny Depp and Amber Heard's highly publicized four-year-long showdown? Ever since this legal battle has started, Johnny Depp has mainly been the one suffering major blow after blow, as he got fired from several large-scale projects, and nearly had his career ruined for life. But unexpectedly, a number of people have recently started to break their silence and started offering proof backing him up, including Disney.

The biggest mass media company reportedly rehired Depp for his mega-popular role Captain Jack Sparrow in the upcoming Pirates of the Caribbean movie. In a turn of events, Amber Heard is now the one on the receiving end of the negativity. The ex-Aquaman star has recently gotten replaced as “Mera” who will now be played by Emilia Clarke in Aquaman 2. But what does Johnny have to say about all this? Does he feel pitty, or is he excited that things are finally going his way?

snippet.localized.title: "She Deserves Jail Time" Johnny Depp Speaks On Amber Heard
snippet.localized.description:
Johnny Depp Reveals What He Think Should Happen To Amber Heard For What She Did.

✅ Subscribe & HIT that notification bell for more Celebrity Content!

Are we finally witnessing the curtains being lowered on Johnny Depp and Amber Heard's highly publicized four-year-long showdown? Ever since this legal battle has started, Johnny Depp has mainly been the one suffering major blow after blow, as he got fired from several large-scale projects, and nearly had his career ruined for life. But unexpectedly, a number of people have recently started to break their silence and started offering proof backing him up, including Disney.

The biggest mass media company reportedly rehired Depp for his mega-popular role Captain Jack Sparrow in the upcoming Pirates of the Caribbean movie. In a turn of events, Amber Heard is now the one on the receiving end of the negativity. The ex-Aquaman star has recently gotten replaced as “Mera” who will now be played by Emilia Clarke in Aquaman 2. But what does Johnny have to say about all this? Does he feel pitty, or is he excited that things are finally going his way?

snippet.title: Celebs.com Hot Clip - Amber Heard & Johnny Depp in "The Rum Diary"
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp's new film, "The Rum Diary," is adapted from the novel by Hunter S. Thompson. Depp portrayed Thompson in "Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas" and the two were close friends until Thompson took his life. Like any good friend, Depp helped pay for Thompson's elaborate cannon-firing funeral, then set about bringing one of the author's written works to life. 

If you're a fan of "Fear and Loathing" then you'll love "The Rum Diary," starring Depp, Aaron Eckhart, Amber Heard and Giovanni Ribisi. 

A friend of Celebs.com, photographer Scott McDermott sent over some gorgeous shots of Amber looking very Marilyn Monroe... or is she summoning a young Kim Basinger? Either way, you can check out the images here: http://www.celebs.com/archives/celebs-com-originals-ammmber-heard-exclusives-by-scott-mcdermott.html

One of the most interesting things to come from the Johnny Depp case that is going on right now is his support system. Because his ex-wife in Amber Heard has been going and proclaiming for years that Johnny Depp has been to her during their time together (which included years of dating and a 1-year marriage for the record). But yet, there have been many, MANY people in the celeb world, his personal life, and the fans who have not believed this since day one. And recently, Depp decided to go and thank those who have supported him. We'll break it down for you. Be sure to like the video and subscribe to the channel!

Click HERE To Enter The GIVEAWAY! https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCbiT0LUIbQj6CQScvWHJeKQ?sub_confirmation=1

snippet.title: Amber Heard Cries as She and Johnny Depp Hand Out Hearing Aids in Brazil
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp and Amber Heard are one Hollywood couple that makes sure to give back. The pair, who are currently in Brazil for the Rock in Rio music festival, took time out of their busy schedules on Thursday to help more than 200 Brazilians hear for the first time. The couple partnered with the Starkey Hearing Foundation to help distribute hearing aids to those in need. Amber fought back tears as she watched Johnny place the life-changing device on a young girl while she wrapped her arms around another. Later that night, Johnny brought some of those fans to watch his band, Hollywood Vampires, perform at the festival so they could hear music for the first time.

snippet.description:
Amber Heard’s third day of cross-examination by Johnny Depp’s lawyers began on Wednesday with Eleanor Laws QC asking about the alleged incident in Australia in March 2015, which Ms Heard has described as a “three-day hostage situation”.

Ms Laws put it to the actress that she “worked yourself into a rage, screaming at him” and threw a glass bottle, adding: “Because you would get yourself into rages on occasions.”

Ms Heard said: “No, I got angry at times but not into a rage that would cause me to throw anything at him.”

snippet.title: Why was Johnny Depp so Confused in his Relationship with Amber Heard? || Psychosis Explained
snippet.description:
https://www.goldcbt.com/  Why would Johnny Depp repeatedly say to news reporters & other people that he was so confused ??? An ongoing feeling of confusion in an adult relationship is a big red flag that you are dealing with the other person's psychosis, which is a common symptom of mental illness or unresolved past trauma.  Psychosis is common with people who are in the BPD, CPTSD, Narcissist & Psychopath personality disorder group.  In this video I briefly explain this phenomenon which is often misunderstood.  

#amberheard #bpd #cptsd #narcissist

snippet.title: Amber Heard golpeaba a Johnny Depp
snippet.description:
El actor Johnny Depp acuso a su exesposa Amber Heard de haber abusado de él, durante su primera declaración en la demanda por difamación en la que reclama a la actriz 50 millones de dólares.

Mientras combinaba las anfetaminas recetadas y las drogas no recetadas con alcohol, la señora Heard cometió innumerables actos de violencia doméstica contra mí, a menudo en presencia de algún testigo, en algunos casos me causó daños corporales graves". Johnny Depp, actor.

En su declaración, Depp afirmó que Heard lo golpeó, le dio un puñetazo y le dio una patada.

Ella también me lanzó objetos con frecuencia, como botellas pesadas, latas de refrescos, velas encendidas, controles remotos de televisores y latas de disolvente de pintura, que me hirieron gravemente". Johnny Depp, actor.

El actor, de 55 años, negó las acusaciones de Heard, cuando fue al juzgado en mayo de 2016, para obtener una orden de alejamiento temporal, pues aseguró que acudió con moratones pintados que los testigos y las cámaras de vigilancia demostraron que no tenía.

Cabe destacar que en 2016, Depp dijo que decidió divorciarse de Heard después de un incidente en el que encontró heces en su cama.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp vs Amber Heard, Roman Polanski Extradition & Facebook Crime Photos
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp’s wife, Amber Heard, has accused Depp of domestic violence and now believes his team has started a social media war attempting to refute her allegations. Will the testimony from Depp’s security guards hinder Heard’s testimony? We look into the allegations further with child protection and national security consultant Francey Hakes. Hakes also breaks down the new extradition attempts against Roman Polanski, the responsibility of Facebook in regards to a Texas man accused of killing his girlfriend and posting the crime photos online and lastly, the sexual assault and racial attacks on an Idaho football player in this episode of Crime Time hosted by Allison Hope Weiner. 

GUEST BIO:
Francey Hakes is a child protection and national security consultant. Former federal prosecutor and first National Coordinator for Child Exploitation Prevention and Interdiction.

snippet.title: AMBER HEARD Threw 'Haymaker' Punch At JOHNNY DEPP
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp has stated that his ex wife Amber Heard threw a haymaker punch at him for reading in bed!!

First Heard left feces in their bed and now Amber Heard has thrown a haymaker punch at Johnny Depp.

Actor Johnny Depp has said his ex-wife Amber Heard’s allegations of domestic violence “mirrored” what he claims was her abuse towards him.

The Pirates Of The Caribbean star told the high court in London that “it seemed like everything she would accuse me of was something she had done to me”.

Depp (57) also accused Heard (34) of throwing a “haymaker” punch at him during a row after her 30th birthday party, hours after he had learned during a “bad” business meeting that he had lost $650 million (about €570 million).

The Hollywood actor made the claims on Monday during his fifth day of evidence in his libel action against the Sun newspaper.

Amber Heard sometimes had bruises and burns on her arm as well as marks on her face during her four-year relationship with Johnny Depp, her younger sister has told the high court in London.

Whitney Henriquez said the Pirates of the Caribbean star was “incredibly jealous and possessive” and would get “paranoid”, often smashing or destroying Heard’s mobile. “She was constantly getting new phones because Johnny would trash [them].”

Depp, 57, is suing the Sun’s publisher, News Group Newspapers, and its executive editor, Dan Wootton, over an article that called him a “wife beater” and referred to “overwhelming evidence” that he had attacked Heard. Depp denies ever hitting Heard, 34, who has submitted details of 14 occasions during their relationship when she claims he assaulted her.

snippet.title: Day Two: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard arrive at the High Court
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp has been accused of slapping  Amber Heard three times after she laughed at his 'Wino Forever' tattoo that he had changed from Winona Ryder's name on the second day of his blockbuster libel case. The Hollywood legend, 57, is suing The Sun newspaper after it labelled him a 'wife beater'. Yesterday he denied the claims and branded them 'sick' and 'completely untrue'. Today Depp, who is being cross-examined at the High Court in London, was asked by The Sun's lawyer Sasha Wass QC if he had taken cocaine at the time of the alleged incident in March 2013. Ms Wass put it to Depp that the actor first hit Heard, 34, in early 2013 - one of 14 separate allegations of domestic violence, all denied by  Depp, relied on by The Sun in their defence.

JOHNNY DEPP WINS CASE AGAINST AMBER HEARD

Several months after losing a case against british newspaper Johnny Depp has won a legal battle against his former wife.Johnny Depp or Amber Heard have not reacted to the ruling on their social media accounts. The actor has been granted a motion to establish whether or not she donated her $7 million divorce settlement to a charity.The ruling given by a judge in New York said American Civil Liberties Union must provide documentation that confirms whether Amber Heard gave the nonprofit organisation a donation from the $7 million she received in her divorce settlement from Depp as well as the Childrens Hospital Los Angeles. Mr Depp is happy with the court decision.

snippet.title: AMBER HEARD MISSHANDELT: Johnny Depp gerät vor Gericht im Kreuzverhör unter Druck
snippet.description:
Schauspieler Johnny Depp hat bei einer Zeugenaussage vor Gericht weitere Einblicke in seine jahrelange Drogensucht gegeben. 2014 habe er versucht, von dem Opioid Oxycodon loszukommen, daher könne die rückblickende Beschreibung seiner Ex-Frau Amber Heard korrekt sein, dass er damals «ausgeflippt» sei, sagte Depp am Donnerstag vor dem High Court in London. Abermals stritt er ab, körperlich gewalttätig gewesen zu sein. Depp geht juristisch gegen die britische Boulevardzeitung «The Sun» und deren Verlag News Group Newspapers vor, weil die Zeitung Depp 2018 in einem Artikel als «Ehefrauen-Schläger» bezeichnet hat.

«Ich erinnere mich, dass ich starke Schmerzen und nicht zu kontrollierende Spasmen und so hatte ... Ausflippen könnte also ein Wort sein, das korrekt ist», sagte Depp mit Blick auf den Entzugsversuch. «Mir ging es nicht gut. Ich war wahrscheinlich am tiefsten Punkt, an dem ich je in meinem Leben war.»

Im Kreuzverhör warf ihm die «Sun»-Anwältin Sasha Wass vor, seine Ex-Frau zu dem Zeitpunkt geschlagen zu haben. Der Hollywood-Star beschuldigte Heard daraufhin, Lügen zu erzählen. Er habe zwar Gegenstände zerstört, räumte er ein, das sei aber besser, «als es an der Person auszulassen, die ich liebe». Er stritt ab, körperlich gewalttätig gewesen zu sein und sich unter dem Einfluss von Drogen und Alkohol nun nicht mehr daran erinnern zu können. «Sicher gab es Blackouts, aber in jedem Blackout gibt es kleine Erinnerungsschnipsel.»

Depp hat bereits an zwei vorherigen Prozesstagen zurückgewiesen, Heard geschlagen zu haben. Am Mittwoch räumte er im Verhör mit Wass ein, unter Alkohol und Drogen womöglich Dinge getan zu haben, an die er sich nicht mehr erinnern könne. «Ich bin aber sicherlich keine gewalttätige Person, besonders nicht mit Frauen», so Depp.

In vorangegangenen Aussagen sagte er bereits, über die Jahre habe er verschiedene Drogen genommen, darunter Marihuana, Kokain, LSD, Ecstasy und verschreibungspflichtige Medikamente. Sein Drogenkonsum habe im Alter von elf Jahren begonnen.

Amber Heard nimmt an dem auf drei Wochen angesetzten Prozess teil und es wird erwartet, dass sie ebenfalls aussagt. Der Fall hat sich zu einem bitteren Rosenkrieg zwischen den beiden entwickelt. Sie werfen sich gegenseitig Gewalt, Kontrollsucht und Hinterlist vor.


#jonnydepp #eifersucht #amberheard

snippet.title: JOHNNY DEPP AND AMBER HEARD: THEIR TRUE LOVE STORY
snippet.description:
PLEASE, READ ALL THE DISCRIPTION BELOW. IT'S IMPORTANT. THANKS.

This video shows just facts. Johnny Depp and Amber Heard do make a beautiful, lovely and discreet couple and they just want to live their lives, and their love. They don't care about what people think or about the ridiculous made up tabloid stories.

They like to stay with each other, they like to do things together. And they like also to wear each other's things. It's not corny. It's romantic, poetic, beautiful and pure. That's what couples in love use to do.

It's a serious relationship, not just a fling or an affair, like some people thought last year. And that "on-and-off" thing was also a tabloid lie. They've  been together for almost two years, as you can see in the pictures we have on this video.

And forget words like: "cheater", "home wrecker", "mid life crisis", "gold digger" and things like that, because all those things come from tabloids and all those rumors are absolutely untrue, as this video proves to you.

The former couples (Johnny and Vanessa, Amber and Tasya) just grew apart. And Amber has NOTHING to do with Johnny's breakup with Vanessa, in 2011.

In June-2012 Johnny Depp's publicist Robin Baum confirmed that he had split from Vanessa and that it was amicable. The confirmation came many months after the fact.

We have Johnny's own words. He gave an interview to Rolling Stone Magazine (July-2013 issue) and told that his relationship with his ex was difficult. "It was not easy for me, not easy for her." He explained: "the trajectory of that relationship... you play it out until it goes, and a thing takes to another". He also said that the end of the relationship doesn't stop the fact that "you care about that person, that their are the mother of your kids, you'll always know that person, and their will always be in your life because of those kids". So, he said that he made things as better as possible. See? He respects his ex. He is a gentleman, he never said bad things about any of his exes. EVER. And the children accepted that break ups are "part of life" (as Johnny said). "It's normal. You don't have to hate each other", he said on a TV show.

Vanessa also said that the relationship was difficult. She said that even though she was still in love with him, she was unhappy. She also said that something didn't work in their relationship from the beginning. "If something in your love doesn't work in the beginning, it will never work". She said in a French interview recently that "love in first sight exists but soon or later it ends". And once she said, two years ago (when, as  we know, they were breaking up) that their relationship was complicated, like a Rubik cub. 

All these proves once for all that Johnny's former relationship did not work (and it seems that there were serious problems and differences since the beginning) it was not Amber's falt. Not at all.

Amber appeared in Johnny's life to bring him love, happiness, health, youth, spice and warm!

snippet.title: Day Six: Actors Johnny Depp and Amber Heard arrive at the High Court
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp arrived at the High Court today to hear evidence from his security team and property managers as his high-profile libel case continues over allegations of domestic violence by his ex-wife Amber Heard. The court is due to hear evidence from Malcolm Connolly, part of Depp's security team; Tara Roberts, the property manager at Depp's Bahamas home; and Hilda Vargas, Depp's housekeeper at his Los Angeles properties. Heard's assistant Savannah McMillan is also due to appear, one day after Depp, 57, finally finished giving evidence and claimed that allegations of domestic violence made by Heard, 34, 'mirrored' her abuse towards him. On the final day of his evidence at the Royal Courts of Justice in London yesterday in his libel case against The Sun, Depp said: 'It seemed like everything she would accuse me of was something she had done to me.'

snippet.title: Day Twelve: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard arrive at the High Court
snippet.description:
Ms Heard, who started her third day of evidence this morning, claims the megastar actor, 57, and his allies have tried to 'embarrass and harass me and the people around me, including potential witnesses' ahead of his extraordinary London libel trial. In a new witness statement published today, the actress, 34, said she was 'eager for this trial to proceed' claiming her ex-husband's 'campaign has affected my professional life, my personal life and my well-being. It has been extremely upsetting'. She said: 'Johnny is so much more powerful than I am, in every way: physically, financially, and professionally. By leaving him I escaped the physical abuse, but for the past four years he has used his power and resources to continue the harassment and abuse'. She added: 'I have been subjected to a campaign of targeted online abuse on social media, as well as online petitions calling for me to be removed from any future sequel to Aquaman and from my association with L'Oreal'. Today Ms Heard is expected to give her final evidence with her ex-husband feet away as the biggest English libel trial of the 21st century comes to a head.
